  "url": "https://www.tamilmirror.lk/\u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd/\u0b87\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0baf-\u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1-\u0b86\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc1-110-\u0bb5\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd-\u0b89\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1/175-299993",
  "time_ut": 1657306025,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u2019\u0b87\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0baf \u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b86\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc1 110 \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b89\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'Today's protest has 110 percent support'",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The oppression and aggression against us has today turned against the majority community. But we stand with you in today's struggles. Tamil National Federation Member of Parliament MA Sumanthran said that you have our 110 percent support.",
        "Today's young society is forward thinking that everyone is equal. They also expect us to show that we are honest. The President was elected by the overwhelming majority of the people of the country.",
        "Similarly, the people also elected a government with a strength close to two-thirds majority. In two years, the entire country is urging them to resign. Also, people are insisting that there should be a change in mechanism. Didn't they know then that they are corrupt and incompetent? Why did they choose knowingly?",
        "When the Separate Sinhala Act was passed 66 years ago, our leaders first started the protest, and then no one joined hands with us. I ask anyone who raises their voice today, where did you go that day? Even when oppression, racism and military aggression turned towards us, we opposed them. Today it's back to you. We are with you even now.",
        "We stand with you completely. You have our support 110 percent. But what are we going to do after this revolution? This is our question. Parliament should be dissolved first.",
        "Parliament is still dissolved. No one knows who is on which side, so only official notification is required. The government also does not have a mandate from the people, and the president does not have a mandate from the people. Therefore Parliament should be dissolved and a new mandate should be given to the people. People must give a new mandate. Change must be built into existing mechanisms. It cannot be created from outside.",
        "I am with you in today's crisis. Bigotry and racism are the biggest problems in this country. When Gotabaya Rajapaksa was elected as President, we reported him as a racist. Today, when the stomach is different, fuel and food are not available, most of the people say that they do not want racism. He said why did you not understand these while choosing him."
      ],
